From 0607c30228d691d60887c1be392fe1c97f393548 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 20:22:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.1: Add useCurrentUser hook, consolidate 16
 base44.auth.me() calls
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Introduces a shared react-query-backed hook as the single source of
truth for the authenticated user. Replaces the pattern of every page
doing its own useState+useEffect+base44.auth.me() with a cached,
deduplicated query.

Hook (src/hooks/useCurrentUser.js):
- useCurrentUser(options) — primary read hook, 5 min staleTime
- useInvalidateCurrentUser() — invalidate after mutations
- useRefetchCurrentUser() — imperative fresh fetch

Migrated call sites (12 files, 16 base44.auth.me() calls removed):
- src/App.jsx (AuthenticatedApp) — uses { enabled } to wait for auth preflight
- src/pages/Dashboard.jsx
- src/pages/Messages.jsx
- src/pages/ServiceRequests.jsx
- src/pages/DealBoard.jsx
- src/pages/TCProfilePage.jsx
- src/pages/PMLProfilePage.jsx
- src/pages/InvestorProfilePage.jsx
- src/pages/SupportTickets.jsx
- src/pages/admin/SupportTickets.jsx
- src/pages/Onboarding.jsx — 4 call sites using refetch/invalidate helpers
- src/lib/PageNotFound.jsx — was using its own ['user'] queryKey, now shares

Intentionally NOT migrated:
- src/lib/AuthContext.jsx — the auth bootstrap integrates tightly with
  public_settings + authError lifecycle; migration would expand scope
  meaningfully. Left as-is for a future follow-up.

Net effect:
- Route transitions no longer trigger redundant user refetches
- Loading state is consistent across the app (isLoading from react-query)
- PageNotFound no longer uses a fragmented queryKey
- Onboarding's write-then-read patterns use the imperative refetch helper

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
- npm run build: succeeds
- 16 -> 3 base44.auth.me() call sites (2 in the hook itself + 1 in
  AuthContext bootstrap that was intentionally left alone)
